# General Project Specifications

## Technology Stack
- Python 3.10
- Conda management dependency
- Using Bash Script

## Code Style
- Keep the code concise and readable
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add appropriate comments to explain complex logic
- Follow the official style guidelines for each language

## Project Structure
- Maintain clear project structure and adhere to modular principles
- Related functions should be placed in the same directory
- Use appropriate directory naming to reflect its contents

## General Development Principles
- Write testable code
- Avoid duplicate code (DRY principle)
- Prioritize the use of existing libraries and tools to avoid reinventing the wheel
- Consider the maintainability and extensibility of the code

